[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three charged over Belfast ram-raid crime spree

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three people arrested on suspicion of involvement with a spate of crimes are to appear in court.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A stolen car was rammed into thbe front window of a clothes shop on the Lisburn Road in south Belfast early on Saturday and stock was taken.
The car had been stolen a few hours earlier during a burglary in Holywood, County Down.
The three people were arrested after a serious collision on Cliftonville Drive in north Belfast.
The accused, described by police as an adult and two juveniles, are to appear in court on Monday charged with a number of offences including burglary and aggravated vehicle-taking.
